This is **TRUE**. The dead zone code looks like:
```
if (abs(diff) > 50) {
  int angle = map(diff, -1023, 1023, 0, 180);
  myServo.write(angle);
}
```
Under 50 difference → ignore. Over 50 → track. Servo jitter disappears. This concept is called a **dead band** in control engineering.
